default About Crisisdefault10.1 defaultCrisis is the national charity for single homeless people. We are dedicated to ending homelessness by delivering life-changing services and campaigning for change. Our innovative education, employment, housing and well-being services address individual needs and help people to transform their lives
default. 
default&#xa0;
default10.2 defaultCrisis has worked to open up access to the private rented sector for homeless and vulnerable housed people 
defaultacross 
defaultthe 
defaultUK
default since 1997. With the support of the Department of Communities and Local Government Crisis manages the Private Rented Sector Access Development Programme which funds and supports local community 
defaultorganisations
default across 
defaultEngland
default to help single homeless people find and then keep a private rented home. We have already worked with 
default120 schemes across 
defaultEngland
default helping 4000 into accommodation. 
defaultWe also work with the Scottish Government to support the development of rent deposit guarantee schemes.
